{{Infobox scientist |name = Carl von Voit |image =Carl von Voit.jpg |image_size =200px |caption = Carl von Voit |birth_date = 31 October 1831 |birth_place = [[Amberg]] |death_date = {{death-date and age|31 January 1908|31 October 1831}} |death_place = [[Munich]] |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = [[Germany|German]] |ethnicity = |field = [[physiology]] |work_institutions = |alma_mater = [[University of Munich]] |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = [[dietetics]] |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }}'''Carl [[von]] Voit''' (31 October 1831 – 31 January 1908) was a [[Germany|German]] [[physiologist]] and [[dietitian]]. == Biography == Voit was born in [[Amberg]]. From 1848 to 1854 he studied at the universities of [[University of Munich|Munich]] and [[University of Würzburg|Würzburg]]. At Munich, his teachers were [[Justus von Liebig]] and [[Max Joseph von Pettenkofer|Max Joseph Pettenkofer]], and at Würzburg, he was a pupil of [[Albert von Kölliker]]. In 1855 he furthered his education at the [[University of Göttingen]] under chemist [[Friedrich Wohler]], and in 1856/57 served as an assistant to [[Theodor Ludwig Wilhelm von Bischoff|Theodor von Bischoff]] in Munich. In 1857 he obtained his [[habilitation]], and from 1863 was a full professor of physiology as well as curator of the physiological collection at the University of Munich.<ref>[http://drw.saw-leipzig.de/31197 VOIT, Carl Michael von Voit] drw.saw-leipzig.de</ref>
== Contributions == Carl von Voit is considered by many to be the "father" of modern [[dietetics]]. As a [[chemist]] and physiologist, he found that the amount of [[nitrogen]] in excreted [[urea]] is a measure for the [[protein turnover]]. Using a [[respiration chamber]], he could characterize the significance of individual nutrients, known as ''Voitsche Kostmaß''.
He was also a successful teacher, attracting international students to the University of Munich and thus significantly influencing the US nutritionist, among others. One of his better known German pupils was [[Max Rubner]].
Carl von Voit died in [[Munich]].
The [[German Nutrition Society]] awards the Carl-von-Voit-medal since 1961.
== Works == * ''Die Gesetze der Ernährung des Fleischfressers'' (Leipzig 1860) * ''Über die Wirkung des Kochsalzes, des Kaffees und der Muskelbewegung auf den Stoffwechsel'' (Munich 1860) * ''Über die Kost in öffentlichen Anstalten'' (Munich 1876) * ''Untersuchung der Kost in einigen öffentlichen Anstalten'' (Munich 1877) * ''Über die Entwickelung der Erkenntnis'' (Munich 1879) * ''Physiologie des allgemeinen Stoffwechsels und der Ernährung'' (volume 6, first section of [[Ludimar Hermann]]'s "Handbuch der Physiologie", Leipzig 1881) * ''Zeitschrift für Biologie'' (as publisher, together with [[Ludwig von Buhl]] und [[Max von Pettenkofer]]) ==References== {{Wikisource author}} *{{cite journal |last=Lusk |first= |authorlink= |date=February 1908 |title=CARL VON VOIT |journal=[[Science (journal)|Science]] |volume=27 |issue=686 |pages=315–316 | publisher = | location = | pmid = 17770692 |doi = 10.1126/science.27.686.315-a | bibcode =1908Sci....27..315L | oclc =| id = | url = | language = | format = | accessdate = | laysummary = | laysource = | laydate = | quote = |first1=G }} *{{cite journal |last=Sigerist |first=H E |authorlink= |year=1989 |title=The history of dietetics. 1941 |journal=[[Gesnerus]] |volume=46 Pt 3–4 |issue= |pages=249–56 | publisher = | location = | pmid = 2696668 | bibcode = | oclc =| id = | url = | language = | format = | accessdate = | laysummary = | laysource = | laydate = | quote = }} *{{cite journal |last=Heyll |first=U |authorlink= |date=December 2007 |title=[The "Fight over the Protein Minimum". The conflict between scientific nutrition teaching and food reform in 19th and 20th century Germany] |journal=[[Dtsch. Med. Wochenschr.]] |volume=132 |issue=51–52 |pages=2768–73 | publisher = | location = | pmid = 18074324 |doi = 10.1055/s-2007-1012767 | bibcode = | oclc =| id = | url = | language = | format = | accessdate = | laysummary = | laysource = | laydate = | quote = }} {{reflist}}
