{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox school | name = Walden's Path School | image = Walden's_Path_School_Logo.png | imagesize = 250px | alt = | caption ="Awakening Intelligence" | established = 2014 | type = [[Private School]] | city = [[Hyderabad]] | state = [[Telangana]] | country = [[India]] |founder = Sunil Mayreddy & Sujana Mayreddy<ref>{{cite web|title=Founder|url=https://waldenspath.com/about-us/|website=waldenspath.com|accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref> |website = {{URL|https://www.waldenspath.com/}} }}
'''Walden's Path School''' is one of the several [[Jiddu Krishnamurti Schools]] located at [[Jubilee Hills]] in [[Hyderabad]], [[India]].<ref name="Bloomberg.com">{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/markets/news/article.asp?docKey=600-201501270513M2______EUPR_____219900001f390bf7_3600-1 |title=Walden’s Path: New International School in India to Introduce Artful Learning Method |publisher=Bloomberg.com |date= | accessdate=2015-01-27}}</ref> It follows Cambridge [[International General Certificate of Secondary Education|IGCSE]] syllabi. The School is inspired by Jiddu Krishnamurti's Educational Philosophy. Walden's Path Kinder enrolls students up to six years of age and The Magnet School enrolls students for grades 1 to 12.<ref name=Admissions>{{cite web|title=Admissions|url=https://waldenspath.com/admissions/|publisher=Walden's Path|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref>
==Philosophy== The school is inspired by [[Jiddu Krishnamurti]]'s philosophy and his life work.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://waldenspath.com/about-us/|title=Walden's Path About us - Walden's Path|work=Walden's Path|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref> Walden’s Path is based on the notion that children need to be able to get to information following their own path, construct and create their own knowledge and paths.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Learning in every corner|journal=Teacher Plus|date=4 January 2016|issue=January 2016|url=http://www.teacherplus.org/2016/january-2016/learning-in-every-corner|accessdate=5 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=An Interesting path To Take|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31809&articlexml=AN-INTERESTING-PATH-TO-TAKE-17042015452026#|accessdate=30 April 2015|issue=Times School|publisher=Times of India|date=17 April 2015}}</ref>
==Walden's Path | The Magnet School== [[The Magnet School]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Magnet School|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/|website=Magnet School|publisher=The Magnet School|accessdate=1 June 2015}}</ref> follows The Studio Approach with Science, Mathematics, Language and Literature. The Magnet School is admitting students in grades 1-4 for the 2016 academic year.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Magnet School at Walden's Path|url=https://waldenspath.com/magnet-school/|website=Walden's Path|publisher=Walden's Path|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref> The Magnet School developed an approach and methodology that enables children to discover multiple ways of solving problems in Mathematics and applying concepts in Science.<ref>{{cite news|title=AN INTERESTING PATH TO TAKE...|url=http://epaperbeta.timesofindia.com/Article.aspx?eid=31809&articlexml=AN-INTERESTING-PATH-TO-TAKE-17042015452026#|accessdate=17 April 2015|issue=Times School|publisher=Times Of India|date=17 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Our Approach|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/approach/|website=The Magnet School|publisher=The Magnet School|accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref>
The Experiential Studio serves grades 1 - IV while The Scholar’s Studio serves grades V - XII.
===Studio Based Learning===
Walden's Path | The Magnet School follows Studio-Based Learning and is inspired by John Dewey’s work and education philosophy. Unlike a lab that uses standardized procedures with set equipment to reproduce a protocol in order to obtain set outcomes, a Studio is a space that invigorates, inspires and provides an opportunity to create, construct and test objectives and hypotheses and analyse data.<ref>{{cite web|title=Studio Based Learning|url=https://www.magnetschool.edu.in/studio-based-learning/|website=www.magnetschool.edu.in|publisher=The Magnet School|accessdate=12 July 2015}}</ref>
